title: Grateful Dead Live at Laguna Seca Recreation Area on 1988-07-31
lineage: Master Cassettes (Maxell MX90) Tascam 112MKII -> Korg MR-1, 1bit 2.8MHz -> USB -> Korg Audio Gate Software 24bit 48KHz -> Wave Lab 6.0 w/UAD -> R8brain for 16bit 44.1KHz sample rate conversion -> Traders Little Helper flac8
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Little Red Rooster*, West L.A. Fadeaway*, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Ramble On Rose, Gentlemen Start Your Engines, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song

Set 2

Hell In A Bucket-> Foolish Heart-> Women Are Smarter-> Terrapin Station-> I Will Take You Home-> Drums-> Space-> The Other One-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: Midnight Hour

Other Artist(s): David Lindley and El Rayo-X and Los Lobos openned. * w/ David Hidalgo.

reviews.review_text: "Dude... my pants..." This musta been recorded "stage left" cause they blew up one of the power mains that day, and the sound cut out for a few seconds... it was a TOTALLY awesome sensation... feeling the music that day... sound board tapes didn't capture the WHOA factor, as they rarely do... Thanks Healy... for thinkin' 'bout US!!!
